Sure! Here's the full and proper command sequence, including installing unzip if it’s not already installed:

---

 ✅ Commands to Install AWS CLI v2 on Ubuntu (with unzip)

bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y unzip

curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"

unzip awscliv2.zip

sudo ./aws/install

aws --version


---

 ✅ What each command does

| Command                     | Purpose                                                       |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| sudo apt update           | Updates your system's package list.                           |
| sudo apt install -y unzip | Installs unzip (required to extract the AWS CLI installer). |
| curl ... -o awscliv2.zip  | Downloads the AWS CLI v2 zip file from Amazon.                |
| unzip awscliv2.zip        | Extracts the installer from the zip file.                     |
| sudo ./aws/install        | Installs AWS CLI system-wide.                                 |
| aws --version             | Verifies the installation and shows the version.              |

---

Let me know if you want to configure AWS credentials after installation!
